						<summary>

						<p>This states that (six pieces of ?) paddy fields (<hi rend="italic">kēdāra-shaṭkam</hi>) situated in Kaliśēkharamaṅgalam a hamlet of Pūḷiyagrāma were endowed for the maintenance of Vēdic scholars residing at Mahākaruṇāgrāma (Peruṅgaruṇai) by (the favour of) Sundarēśa (King Sundara-Pāṇḍya ?)</p>						

